---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTABlock from '../../components/CTABlock.astro';
import FAQBlock from '../../components/FAQBlock.astro';

import { localBusinessSchema as localBusiness } from '../../config/site';
const procedureSchema = { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'MedicalProcedure', 'name': 'Porcelain Veneers', 'description': 'Porcelain veneers are ultra-thin ceramic shells bonded to the front surface of teeth to improve color, shape, size, and alignment for a transformed smile.', 'procedureType': 'https://schema.org/TherapeuticProcedure', 'bodyLocation': 'Mouth', 'followup': 'As recommended by your prosthodontist' };
const faqs = [
  { question: 'How long do porcelain veneers last?', answer: 'High-quality porcelain veneers placed by a prosthodontist typically last 10–20 years. Longevity depends on material quality, bonding technique, your bite, and how well you care for them. Avoiding habits like nail biting, opening packages with your teeth, and wearing a night guard if you grind significantly extends their lifespan. At replacement time, new veneers are fabricated and bonded the same way as the originals.' },
  { question: 'Are porcelain veneers permanent?', answer: 'Yes, in the sense that tooth preparation is required (a small amount of enamel is removed to make room for the veneer) and cannot be undone. Veneers themselves will eventually need replacement after 10–20 years, but the tooth preparation is irreversible. This is an important consideration in your decision — which is why consultation with a prosthodontist who can thoroughly evaluate your specific teeth and bite is essential before committing.' },
  { question: 'Does the veneer procedure hurt?', answer: 'The preparation appointment involves mild tooth reduction under local anesthesia, so you should feel no pain. Temporary veneers are placed between appointments. Some patients experience temporary sensitivity to temperature in the first few days after final placement as the teeth adjust to the bonded porcelain. This typically resolves within 1–2 weeks.' },
  { question: 'How much do porcelain veneers cost in Huntington Beach?', answer: 'Porcelain veneers typically range from $1,500–$3,000 per tooth depending on material, complexity, and lab quality. Most veneer cases address 8–10 teeth for a complete smile transformation, representing a total investment of $12,000–$30,000. Dental insurance does not typically cover veneers as they are considered cosmetic. Financing options are available through our practice.' },
  { question: 'Can I whiten my veneers if they stain?', answer: 'Porcelain veneers are highly stain-resistant and do not respond to whitening agents. This is actually an advantage: once shade-matched to your ideal white, your veneers maintain that color indefinitely. If your natural teeth behind the veneers or adjacent unveneered teeth stain, whitening those teeth may be appropriate to maintain color consistency.' },
  { question: 'Who is a good candidate for porcelain veneers?', answer: 'Good candidates have structurally sound teeth with adequate enamel for bonding, minimal bite issues (severe grinding can fracture veneers), and specific aesthetic concerns: discoloration that doesn\'t respond to whitening, irregular tooth shape or size, minor crowding or gaps, or chips. Patients with active decay, gum disease, or severe misalignment typically need those issues addressed before veneers are placed.' },
];
const faqSchema = { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'FAQPage', 'mainEntity': faqs.map(f => ({ '@type': 'Question', 'name': f.question, 'acceptedAnswer': { '@type': 'Answer', 'text': f.answer } })) };
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Porcelain Veneers Huntington Beach | Cosmetic Dentist HB, CA"
  description="Porcelain veneers in Huntington Beach from a certified prosthodontic specialist. Transform your smile in 2 visits. Natural, durable, beautiful results. Call (714) 846-1386."
  schema={[localBusiness, procedureSchema, faqSchema]}
>
  <section class="bg-surface-2 py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <div class="text-brand-teal text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">Porcelain Veneers — Huntington Beach</div>
        <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6 leading-tight">
          Porcelain Veneers in Huntington Beach —<br />
          <span class="text-brand-teal">Transform Your Smile in Two Visits</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-mid-gray text-lg leading-relaxed mb-8">
          Porcelain veneers are ultra-thin ceramic shells that reshape, whiten, and harmonize your smile — designed by a prosthodontist who understands both the art and science of dental aesthetics.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
          <a href="/schedule" class="btn-accent text-base px-8 py-4 font-semibold text-center">Book Free Consultation</a>
          <a href="/veneers/smile-makeover" class="btn-secondary text-base px-8 py-4 font-semibold text-center">Smile Makeover Options</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="section-heading mb-6">What Are Porcelain Veneers?</h2>
        <p class="text-neutral-mid leading-relaxed mb-4 text-lg">
          A porcelain veneer is a thin shell of high-strength dental ceramic — typically 0.5–1.0mm thick — that is permanently bonded to the front surface of a tooth. Veneers can change the color, shape, length, and texture of your teeth, producing a complete smile transformation while preserving the underlying tooth structure.
        </p>
        <p class="text-neutral-mid leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Unlike dental crowns that cover the entire tooth, veneers cover only the visible front surface, requiring minimal tooth preparation. Unlike composite bonding that uses tooth-colored resin, porcelain veneers are fabricated in a dental laboratory from ceramic that is stronger, more stain-resistant, and more aesthetically refined than any chairside material can achieve.
        </p>
        <p class="text-neutral-mid leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Porcelain veneers are particularly effective for: teeth with intrinsic staining that doesn't respond to whitening (tetracycline staining, fluorosis), teeth with irregular shape or size, minor spacing or crowding, worn or chipped tooth edges, and patients who want a dramatic aesthetic improvement without orthodontics. They are also the finishing touch in many <a href="/veneers/smile-makeover" class="text-brand-blue hover:underline">complete smile makeover</a> cases.
        </p>

        <h2 class="section-subheading mt-10 mb-6">The Veneer Process: Two Primary Appointments</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="text-brand-blue font-semibold text-sm uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Visit 1 — Design & Preparation</div>
            <h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-brand-navy mb-3">Smile Design & Tooth Preparation</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-mid text-sm leading-relaxed">Digital impressions and photographs capture your current smile. Dr. Favian Cheong designs your new tooth shapes using digital smile design software. A conservative amount of enamel is removed from the tooth surface. Temporary veneers are placed so you can preview the result and provide feedback before the final restorations are made.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="text-brand-blue font-semibold text-sm uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Visit 2 — Placement</div>
            <h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-brand-navy mb-3">Veneer Bonding & Placement</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-mid text-sm leading-relaxed">Your custom porcelain veneers arrive from the lab. Each veneer is tried in dry, evaluated for fit and shade, adjusted as needed, then bonded with high-strength dental adhesive under a curing light. Final bite adjustment and polishing complete the appointment. Most patients leave their veneer placement appointment with an enormous smile.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="section-subheading mt-10 mb-4">Why Choose a Prosthodontist for Veneers in Huntington Beach?</h2>
        <p class="text-neutral-mid leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Veneers are an artistic and technical procedure that demands deep expertise in dental aesthetics, tooth preparation design, and material science. Prosthodontists receive specific training in all three areas during their residency. The difference in outcome between a well-designed veneer case and a mediocre one is significant — veneers placed without proper attention to translucency, tooth proportions, gum level, and bite can look artificial, feel uncomfortable, or fail prematurely.
        </p>
        <p class="text-neutral-mid leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Dr. Favian Cheong applies prosthodontic-level precision to every veneer case: from facial analysis and digital smile planning to material selection and bonding protocol. We use premium-quality porcelain from leading dental laboratories that match the optical properties of natural enamel. The result is veneers that look and feel genuinely natural — because they are designed by a specialist.
        </p>
        <p class="text-neutral-mid leading-relaxed">
          Explore our <a href="/veneers/porcelain" class="text-brand-blue hover:underline">porcelain veneer details page</a>, learn about <a href="/cosmetic-dentistry" class="text-brand-blue hover:underline">all cosmetic dentistry options</a>, or schedule your consultation to see what veneers can do for your smile.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-8">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <FAQBlock faqs={faqs} heading="Porcelain Veneer FAQ — Huntington Beach" />
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8"><CTABlock /></div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
